JOHANNESBURG - Former Western Cape police commissioner Arno Lamoer will not be appealing his corruption sentence. He and two other senior police officers will now start their stint at Malmesbury prison on Monday. Last week, Lamoer and his long-time friend Salim Dawjee, were sentenced an effective six years in jail. READ:Â Lamoer sentence applauded Lamoer was found guilty on a single charge of corruption, while Dawjee was found guilty of corruption and defeating the ends of justice. Two other police officers were sentenced to two and four years respectively. Dawjee is the only one applying for leave to appeal his sentence. That case starts on Monday. eNCA